<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><?workdir /C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\temp\temp20190509171902990\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling?><?workdir-uri file:/C:/Git/XDocs-DITA-OT-185/XDocs-DITA-OT-185/DITA-OT1.8.5/temp/temp20190509171902990/Trident/device/devspec/error_handling/?><?path2project ..\?><?path2project-uri ../?><topic xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" class="- topic/topic " xml:lang="en-US" base="base" id="xd_d3b8a21dc0006870--4175b2bf-15fea5042d3--7fab" domains="(topic hi-d)                             (topic ut-d)                             (topic indexing-d)                            (topic hazard-d)                            (topic abbrev-d)                            (topic pr-d)                             (topic sw-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic struct-d)                            (topic firmware-d)                            (topic pmcrevhis-d)   " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="topic:1;10:468">
   <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="title:1;13:26">TLP Credit Timeout</title>
   <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="body:1;16:32">
      <p class="- topic/p " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="p:1;20:29">The switch egress ports receive credits for every TLP that is sent. If the switch sends a TLP and does not receive a credit for it, traffic will back up and the egress port will become blocked. The stalled traffic resulting from the blocked egress port could eventually lead to completion timeouts on a host issuing traffic to other ports, or even deadlock the switch through head of line blocking. In many cases, a device that stops providing credits for such a long time is likely in a bad state and must be prevented from bringing other parts of the subsystem down.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="p:2;24:29">Switchtec has mechanism that if FC_Updates are received but no credits are returned, the Credit Timeout event is triggered and can be handled as either:</p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="ul:1;28:30">
         <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="li:1;31:26">
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="p:3;34:27">The link is disabled</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="li:2;38:26">
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="p:4;41:27">The link is reset </p>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="- topic/p " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="p:5;47:29">This feature provides a link disable/reset instead of a link retrain, which prevents TLP Timeout within the switch. It is highly recommended that TLP Credit Timeout be enabled.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="p:6;50:29">It is recommended to set the TLP Credit Timeout to a value that is slightly lower then the host or <ph status="deleted" rev="deltaxml-delete" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="ph:1;50:171">endpoint</ph>
         <ph status="new" rev="deltaxml-add" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="ph:2;51:46">Endpoint</ph> completion timeout.</p>
      <note class="- topic/note " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="note:1;55:32">
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="p:7;58:24">The Switchtec Credit Timeout is independent of the DLLP Timeout of PCI Base Specification. When the Switchtec Credit Timeout is triggered, the DLLP Timeout of PCI Base Specification may be triggered many times independently which will retrain the link.</p>
      </note>
      <section audience="MSCCInternal" class="- topic/section " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="section:1;64:35">
         <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="title:2;67:32">Internal Notes</title>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_tlp_credit_timeout.xml" xtrc="p:8;70:24">To mitigate these issues on the host, Switchtec starts a system-configurable global count timer which will continuously roll over to trigger timeout events at the end of timeout window. If credits are not received before the timeout event happens and there is pending TLP to be sent, an interrupt will be fired and processed by the switch management firmware. This interrupt provides the firmware with an opportunity to handle the blocked egress port gracefully, potentially avoiding any issues on the host. Also, for debug purpose, you can choose to disable the DLLP Timeout.</p>
      </section>
